                      <span>2000-02-28</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I found this work fantastically helpful in locating and reading the gist of all the important cases that the Supreme Court has decided.  Just a little complaint, however:  the index of cases, said to be complete, is  not.  Loewe v. Lawlor, described on p. 163, for instance, is not listed in  the index of cases.  Unfortunately, I also found a few other cases which,  though treated in the book, are inexplicably missing from this index.</span>
                  
              
